BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pHG9Y8FAaBlzbOCGNc_Wy
SUMMARY:Panel Discussion – PLACEHOLDER: Roots\, Rupture + Regeneration
DTSTAMP:20260301T153235Z
DTSTART:20260301T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a community conversation held in conjunction with t
	he current exhibit at Columbia City Gallery\, PLACEHOLDER: Roots\, Rupture
	 + Regeneration. This gathering brings together voices from across communi
	ties and organizations engaged in local place keeping and anti-displacemen
	t efforts. Moderator: Lia Yaranon Hall\, Curator Featuring Panelists: Cynt
	hia Brothers\, Vanishing Seattle Asia Tail\, yəhaw̓ Indigenous Creatives C
	ollective Daniel Smith\, Artist Mateo Quispe\, Poet Laureate of Auburn Jam
	es Lovell\,Chief Seattle Club As the One Seattle Comprehensive Plan moves 
	forward—shaping how neighborhoods grow\, change\, and endure for generatio
	ns—this moment invites reflection and action. Together\, we will explore t
	hemes of rematriation\, cultural stewardship\, and community self-determin
	ation\, centering lived experience\, collective memory\, and community-led
	 futures. This event offers space for dialogue\, listening\, and connectio
	n across disciplines and communities working to protect cultural presence 
	and belonging in Southeast Seattle and beyond.\n\nhttps://rainierartscente
	r.org/events/columbia-city-gallery-panel-discussion/\n\nFrom Rainier Arts 
	Center
URL:https://rainierartscenter.org/events/columbia-city-gallery-panel-discus
	sion/
LOCATION:Auditorium\, Rainier Arts Center\, 3515 S Alaska St\, Seattle\, WA
	 98118
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:rainier-arts-center
CATEGORIES:Rainier Arts Center
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
