UID:3FzkJFMCoFgIISJP_2qbS
SUMMARY:SafeCampus Violence Prevention and Response Training
DTSTAMP:20260301T153235Z
DTSTART:20260304T223000Z
DESCRIPTION:Wednesday\, Mar 4\, 2026\, 2:30 - 4 p.m. PST\n\nDuring this int
	eractive training\, we ask participants to consider their unique role in p
	reventing violence at the University of Washington. This training has been
	 adapted to consider the remote academic environments that many staff\, st
	udents\, and faculty are currently experiencing. We will explore mental he
	alth and warning signs of different forms of violence including\; workplac
	e violence\, relationship violence\, sexual harassment\, and stalking. We 
	will briefly practice in-person and remote bystander intervention techniqu
	es and build your understanding of UW resources.\n\nClick the link below t
	o register for this training.\n\nCampus room: Online Zoom Training Accessi
	bility Contact:  safecampus@uw.edu Event Types: Information Sessions\, Lec
	tures/Seminars\, Workshops More info:  forms.office.com…\n\nhttps://seatod
	ay.6amcity.com/events/#/details/safecampus-violence-prevention-and-respons
	e-training/17922579/2026-03-04T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
