BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:L_ZHJnai8drCo2rQ6aYM3
SUMMARY:Off Book Productions Presents: James and the Giant Peach
DTSTAMP:20260301T153236Z
DTSTART:20260314T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a juicy adventure bursting with imagination! James 
	and the Giant Peach Jr. brings Roald Dahl’s beloved story to life in a del
	ightful\, high-energy musical for all ages. Follow young James as he escap
	es a dreary life and embarks on an unforgettable journey across the ocean 
	inside a giant peach—alongside a crew of quirky\, lovable insect friends. 
	Packed with catchy songs\, colorful characters\, and plenty of heart\, thi
	s fun-filled production is a sweet treat the whole family will love. Buy T
	ickets\n\nhttps://rainierartscenter.org/events/off-book-productions-presen
	ts-james-and-the-giant-peach/\n\nFrom Rainier Arts Center
URL:https://rainierartscenter.org/events/off-book-productions-presents-jame
	s-and-the-giant-peach/
LOCATION:Auditorium\, Rainier Arts Center\, 3515 S Alaska St\, Seattle\, WA
	 98118
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:rainier-arts-center
CATEGORIES:Rainier Arts Center
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6ecpplFKNC0EzALe-AuRi
SUMMARY:Native Art Market and Open House
DTSTAMP:20260301T153236Z
DTSTART:20260314T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Mark your calendars and bring a friend — March 13th is going to
	 be an unforgettable night at Native Action Network! Native Action Network
	 is proud to host a vibrant Native Art Market and an Open House Celebratio
	n as we officially unveil our new expanded office space to the community\n
	\nLocation: Native Action Network                       55 Bell St\, Ste 2
	01                       Seattle\, WA 98121 Date:          March 13th 2026
	 Time:          6:00 pm to 9:00 pm\n\nExpect an amazing evening featuring:
	\n\nIncredible Native artists showcasing one-of-a-kind artwork\n\nA festiv
	e open house\n\nLive Music\n\nDelicious light bites & refreshments includi
	ng Bison Stew\n\nOur new office represents growth\, vision\, and the futur
	e of Native-led organizing\, whether you're coming to support Native artis
	ts\, build connections\, celebrate with us\, or all of the above — we look
	 forward to seeing you.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/n
	ative-art-market-and-open-house/18247148/2026-03-13T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - 
	Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/native-art-market-and-ope
	n-house/18247148/2026-03-13T00
LOCATION:Native Action Network\, 55 Bell St Ste 201\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cdjMT6vihw5US-0WNvm4w
SUMMARY:Young Dragon: A Bruce Lee Story
DTSTAMP:20260301T153236Z
DTSTART:20260314T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Before he was a legend\, Bruce Lee was just a young man trying 
	to figure it all out—right here in Seattle. This action-packed\, soul-sear
	ching story follows the Young Dragon as he navigates a new country and fin
	ds his voice. Through movement\, magic\, and heart\, we meet the human beh
	ind the icon—flawed\, fierce\, and full of possibility. Watch as Lee learn
	s to clear his brain by mimicking the white noise of water and begins fusi
	ng martial arts with philosophy. From street fights in Hong Kong to teachi
	ng self-defense and chasing big dreams\, Bruce’s journey reminds us that f
	inding your way means first figuring out who you are. Come see how Seattle
	 shaped him into a flexible\, fluid\, and flowing master—and how he reshap
	ed the world.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/young-drago
	n-a-bruce-lee-story/18116297/2026-03-13T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cultu
	re
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/young-dragon-a-bruce-lee-
	story/18116297/2026-03-13T00
LOCATION:Seattle Children's Theatre\, 201 Thomas Street\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H15M
END:VEVENT
