BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:e3GeRvZxFNlj1qGD-HlxM
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260301T153236Z
DTSTART:20260314T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-03
	-14T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-03-14T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:s2MPTnado1b2BOI9MeFK2
SUMMARY:SP 202: Fabric Printing
DTSTAMP:20260301T153236Z
DTSTART:20260314T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Do you dream of people wearing your artwork out on the streets?
	 Want to make shirts for your friend’s music project? Level up your fabric
	 printing experience and take home your own printed tote bag in this 3-hou
	r intermediate-level fabric printing class! In this hands-on workshop\, yo
	u’ll explore the use-cases for printing on fabric\, practice properly sett
	ing up on the t-shirt press\, and understand different types of fabrics an
	d inks. Students will receive three tote bags to print on\, or have the op
	tion to bring their own light-colored 100% cotton fabrics to practice on. 
	Students will be printing a Vera specific design\, exclusive to the 202 cl
	ass.\n\nStudents must complete Screenprint 101 before attending this class
	.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/B75453a3bdb7\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/B75453a3bdb7
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
